pageContext.claim: “I have many, many records of the highest stock market. People's 401(k)s are doing better than they have ever done by far. It's up almost 50 percent from the time I am elected president.”
pageContext.analysis: The Dow Jones Industrial Average has increase about 30 percent since Trump took office. He regularly starts his calculations “when he was elected” discounting the last few months of Obama’s last term. But even starting at Election Day, Trump is off. The Dow has increased about 43 percent since then.
